properties.headline: Flood Warning issued January 9 at 3:54PM PST until January 10 at 9:32PM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning has ended for the following rivers in
Washington...

Skokomish River At Potlatch affecting Mason County
Chehalis River Above Grand Mound affecting Grays Harbor and
Thurston Counties

...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in
Washington...

Chehalis River At Porter affecting Grays Harbor County


The next system and cold front Friday will bring 1 to 2 inches of
precipitation. The snow level will start off low at about 1000 feet
but will rise to over 3000 feet as the precipitation comes in. With
the Skokomish River not far below flood stage by that time, there is
a good chance the storm will be enough to drive the Skokomish back up
above flood stage Friday night.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Chehalis River At Porter
* Until Friday evening.
* At  2:45 PM Thursday the stage was 48.8 feet.
* Flood stage is 48.0 feet.
* Minor flooding is occurring and Minor flooding is forecast.
* Forecast...The river crested at 49.0 feet at 7 AM Thursday and will
continue to fall to below flood stage Friday early afternoon.
* Impact...At 48.0 feet, the Chehalis River in Grays Harbor will flood
low pasture lands and some roads. High tidal levels at Aberdeen
will worsen flooding along the lower reaches.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars...vans...or trucks through flooded areas...this is
the cause of most flood related deaths in Washington. Be alert for
rapid changes and monitor developments by listening to NOAA Weather
radio or other local media.
